about.summary: Open source toolkit for helping create serving containers to run on Amazon SageMaker.

name: sagemaker-inference-toolkit
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "sagemaker_inference" %}
{% set version = "1.1.0" %}

package:
  name: "sagemaker-inference-toolkit"
  version: "{{ version }}"

source:
  url: "https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz"
  sha256: e6f881ac04417e0a6c9f953882a145c79a45ab4e0c82de9cfc64dee31669d084

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python
  run:
    - numpy
    - python
    - six
    - typing

test:
  imports:
    - sagemaker_inference

about:
  home: "https://github.com/aws/sagemaker-inference-toolkit/"
  license: "Apache-2.0"
  license_family: "APACHE"
  license_file: "LICENSE"
  summary: "Open source toolkit for helping create serving containers to run on Amazon SageMaker."
  doc_url: "https://pypi.org/project/sagemaker-inference/"
  dev_url: "https://github.com/aws/sagemaker-inference-toolkit/"

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - mwilson8
    - rluria14
